                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Congress suspends tainted leader
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                               
	Bhubaneswar, May 29: The Bijepur MLA of Congress Subala Sahu, charged with sexually exploiting a married woman, has been suspended from the party and district unit.        
	Sahu has been accused of sexually exploiting the woman on numerous occasions in his official residence in Bhubaneswar in December 2006 and at the victims home.         
	The victim, who recently lodged an FIR at the Bijepur police, stated that she met Sahu through Sahus wife  her classmate  and that they were best of friends. Sahu allegedly promised her a job and then lured her with his false promises to Bhubaneswar, where he repeatedly raped her.        
	Later, when she confronted the minister and asked for the promised employment, he allegedly started to threaten her. It was then that the victim revealed her plight to her husband, and he advised her to report the matter to the police.         
	Sahu has rubbished all charges terming it as a political conspiracy. He has added that he is ready to face a crime branch probe to prove his innocence.         
	BJD members, under the leadership of Biju Mahila Janata Dal president and women and child development minister Pramila Mallick, staged a demonstration in front of the Raj Bhavan today demanding Sahus arrest.                                                                                                                                                                         
